KABUL, Nov. 13 (Xinhua) -- An explosion struck a bus on a busy road in the western part of Afghanistan's capital Kabul on Saturday, and the casualties were unknown, an eyewitness said. "We heard a huge blast in the minibus carrying commuters in Mahtab Qala locality of Dashti Bari area. The whole place has now been sealed off by the Taliban's security forces," an eyewitness told Xinhua. The vehicle caught fire, sending a column of thick smoke into the sky and triggering panic, the witness said. Further details are awaited and there is no official announcement yet. No group has claimed responsibility for the attack yet. Enditem